d Intifada, Oslo Process, First Intifada, Thawra, 1967 War, the Naqba, and the Great Arab Revolt of 1936—in their own words. The extraordinary voices of women, children, farmers, fighters, drug dealers, policeman, doctors, and others, spanning the political divide from Salafi Jihadists to Israeli soldiers, bring the Palestinian story to life even as their words sow seeds of hope in the scorched Palestinian earth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPalestinian ArabszGaza Strip. 0aPalestinian ArabszWest Bank. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  acombat.  acontemporary palestine.  aethnic demographic studies.  agovernment and governing.  aground force invasions.  ahistory.  ainternational journalism.  aisrael and palestine history.  aisrael palestine conflict.  ajournalism and politics.  ajournalism in middle east.  alife in middle east.  alife of palestinian.  amiddle east and religion.  amiddle east anthropology.  amiddle east politics.  amiddle east war.  amiddle eastern history.  amilitary drama.  apalestine and refugees.  apalestinian conflict.  apalestinian history.  apeace talks.  apolitics and war.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026427440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094985040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520949850423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520949850/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY